BeanLocationExtensiblePoint - Interface in org.jvault.factory.buildinfo.extensible
Interface about package and class path where Bean is located.

When specifying a package path, the .* expression is available, and if the .* expression is attached to the end of the package path,
all Beans are scanned up or excluded to the leaf directory of the child package path that contains the package path.
(The class path does not allow .* expressions.)

If .* expression is not used, import Bean contained in that folder.

getExcludePackages() - Method in interface org.jvault.factory.buildinfo.extensible.BeanLocationExtensiblePoint
This method must return the package path of the beans to be excluded from the scan.
If an expression is used, exclude the Bean of all leaf package paths, including those package paths.
If not, exclude only the Bean contained in those package paths.

If Empty, No Bean is Excluded.
getExcludePackagesImpl() - Method in class org.jvault.factory.buildinfo.AbstractVaultFactoryBuildInfo
The implementation of this method should return the package path of the beans to exclude from the scan.
* expression can be used at the end of the package path,
and if a .* expression is used at the end of the package path,
the class in the last leaf directory including the path is excluded from empty scanning.
getExcludePackagesImpl() - Method in class org.jvault.factory.buildinfo.PropertiesVaultFactoryBuildInfo

getPackages() - Method in interface org.jvault.factory.buildinfo.extensible.BeanLocationExtensiblePoint
This method must return package paths that contain beans to scan.
If an expression is used, scan the Bean of all leaf package paths, including those package paths.
If not, examine only the Bean contained in those package paths.

If Empty, No Bean is scanned.
getPackagesImpl() - Method in class org.jvault.factory.buildinfo.AbstractVaultFactoryBuildInfo
This method implementation should return package paths where Beans exist.
.* expression can be used at the end of the path,
and if there is a .* expression at the end of the path,
all classes in the last leaf directory including the path are scanned.

BuildInfo will create a class that will be Beans based on this information.
